response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Counting Duplicates\", \"description\": \"Write a function `count_duplicates` that takes a list of integers as input and returns the count of elements that appear more than once in the list.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef count_duplicates(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `lst` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the count of elements that appear more than once in the input list.\", \"code\": \"def count_duplicates(lst: list[int]) -> int:\\n    return len([i for i in set(lst) if lst.count(i) > 1])\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert count_duplicates([1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 0\", \"assert count_duplicates([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3]) == 2\", \"assert count_duplicates([-5, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]) == 0\", \"assert count_duplicates([1, 2, 3, 3, 3, 4, 5, 6]) == 2\"] }"
